{"_id":"mxJTu3Ym7txrMQZw","name":"Commune","permission":{"default":0,"Z8KGVPKcXF0jSV2e":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>When you spend uninterrupted time (an hour or so) in <strong>quiet contemplation</strong> with your deity, you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lose any spells already granted to you</li>\n<li>Are granted new spells of your choice whose total levels don’t exceed your own level +1, and none of which is a higher level than your own level</li>\n<li>Prepare all of your rotes, which never count against your limi</li>\n</ul>","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
{"name":"Providence","permission":{"default":0,"Z8KGVPKcXF0jSV2e":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>You ignore the -1 penalty from up to two spells you maintain. If you maintain more than two you take normal penalties.</p>","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"Serenity","moveType":"advanced"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","_id":"nHgGzKVTi9mdpr1j"}
